## Third-Party Notice

This project is a derivative work inspired by William Gibson's Sprawl Trilogy
(Neuromancer, Count Zero, Mona Lisa Overdrive). All original Gibson concepts
(ICE, cyberspace, console cowboys, constructs, the Sprawl, Freeside, etc.)
remain the intellectual property of William Gibson and his publishers.

This project contains no original Gibson text. Derivative short stories in
`Fiction/derivative/sprawl-trilogy/` are original creations licensed under
the same MIT terms, inspired by but not copying Gibson's prose.